elements.title: Which Communication Provider are you with?

pages.title: Moving to Internet (VoIP) based voice service

elements.name: question3
elements.html: To use BT Digital Voice the Smart Hub 2 is required. You can't use your own router. If you want to use your own router you can either double NAT or move to broadband only package and use a third party VoIP provider.

elements.name: question2
elements.title: How do you want to connect your phone handsets to the service?

choices.text: Use existing phone handsets directly into Smart Hub 2
Use existing phone handsets and connect wirelessly via DECT to Smart Hub 2

elements.name: question4
elements.html:
• Plug your existing handset base unit into the green port on the back of the BT Smart Hub 2. It maybe covered with a sticker. Your telephone wall sockets will no longer work for your phone

  • If it really thought necessary to use corded phones in existing extension wiring, this can be achieved if broadband service is via FTTP (Full Fibre to the home) by simply disconnecting the incoming wires from the master socket and connecting the green socket on the hub to any of the phone sockets with a cord consisting of a phone plug at each end.

    This is more complicated if broadband service is still delivered via the copper pair as the incoming wires cannot be disconnected and the hub still needs to connect to the master socket. It will require a new extension socket to be fitted adjacent to the master socket and the extension wiring transferred to it. This new socket can then be connected to the green socket on the hub as with FTTP.

    Filters are not required anywhere in either situation.

    1571 answering service is enabled by default with DV, therefore if using an answering machine, 1571 should be set to maximum number of rings and the answering machine to a fewer number to allow the answering machine to cut in before 1571.

elements.name: question5
elements.html: You can order an adaptor by either calling up, going to bt.com/dvequipment or texting ADAPTOR to 61088

elements.name: question6
elements.html: You can order the a Digital Voice Handset by either calling up, going to bt.com/dvequipment or texting HANDSET to 61088
